  "prompt": "How do I unlock my laptop keyboard?",
  "response": "There are several ways to unlock a laptop keyboard depending on your specific situation:\n\n1. Check for a keyboard lock function key\n- Many laptops have a special key (often labeled with a keyboard or lock symbol) that can toggle keyboard lock\n- Try pressing: Fn + F7, Fn + F8, or Fn + F9 (varies by laptop model)\n\n2. Restart your laptop\n- Sometimes a simple restart can resolve keyboard lock issues\n\n3. Check keyboard settings\n- On Windows: Control Panel > Keyboard\n- On Mac: System Preferences > Keyboard\n\n4. Check for physical keyboard lock switch\n- Some laptops have a physical switch to lock/unlock the keyboard\n\n5. If using an external keyboard:\n- Ensure it's properly connected\n- Try unplugging and reconnecting\n- Check for a function key that might lock/unlock it\n\n6. Check for software issues\n- Run antivirus scan\n- Update device drivers\n\n7. For specific issues:\n- Windows: Try Ctrl + Alt + Del\n- Mac: Try Force Quit Applications (Command + Option + Esc)\n\nIf none of these work, consider:\n- Consulting your laptop's manual\n- Contacting technical support\n- Having a professional diagnose the issue",
